benchmark_config.jira_title: Implement/Test API: GET /1.0/kb/catalog/priceList - Retrieve priceList for a given subscription and date

covered: Empty Response / no data scenarios (TC04, TC13)
Error handling coverage (HTTP 400/404/422/502/503 scenarios across TC05, TC06, TC07, TC09, TC20)
gaps: Pagination handling for large datasets is not tested
Rate limiting / concurrent requests handling is not tested (beyond general load scenarios)
Caching behavior and caching headers (e.g., ETag, Cache-Control) are not tested
Granular authorization coverage beyond 401 (e.g., 403) not explicitly tested
Performance tests largely cover response time but not automated retry/backoff semantics under transient failures
Additional edge-case tests around partial/malformed query values (beyond TC19) could be expanded
recommendations: Add dedicated pagination tests for /priceList when results span multiple pages
Add rate limiting / throttling tests to verify behavior under rapid successive requests
Add tests validating caching headers (ETag, Cache-Control) and conditional requests
Include scenarios covering alternative authorization failures (e.g., 403) and token refresh flows
Enhance coverage with explicit retry/backoff behavior under transient failures and verify idempotency of repeated GETs
